A man was stabbed and assaulted after getting into an argument with taxi operators in Ballito on Wednesday morning. According to Medi Response, their paramedics were called to an assault incident on the N2 near Tinley Manor. "On arrival of advanced life support paramedics, reports from the scene indicated that taxi operators had allegedly been stopping vehicles to monitor who was onboard," said Medi Response in a statement. "A man and taxi operators became embroiled in an argument allegedly over the fact that he was transporting his own staff. The argument escalated and the man was assaulted and stabbed." Medi Response said the man was stabilised on the scene before handing over the scene to the police for further investigations.